**Item #:** SCP-7000
 
**Object Class:** Euclid
 
**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-7000 is to be held in the office of Ian Vance, former Senior Researcher at Site-74. Salt barriers, protective sigils, and banishment wards shall be implemented at the discretion of the current Site Director. Testing is no longer permitted outside of “Game Session” events.
 
Game Session events must happen at least once a week, and elapse for a strict 4-6 hour window of “play”. Currently, access to SCP-7000 is limited to: Site Director Isreal Ray, Dr. Savanna Clemons, and Junior Researchers Tony McKay & Andre Merritt; two of whom must be present during any Game Session event. In the event these staff members are unavailable, for any reason, replacements must be elected immediately. 

**REVISION 10/2/21:** Israel Ray’s additional access to SCP-7000 has been reduced from 4 hours per week to 1 hour per week. See Addendum-7 for more details. 

**Description:** SCP-7000 is a semi-sentient supernatural entity, believed to be the spirit of former Senior Researcher, Ian Vance, who was killed in a containment breach 8 months prior to the first documented sighting of SCP-7000. (See Addendum-3 for more details) SCP-7000 has been shown to recreate the moments of its death at irregular intervals. These events have been shown to last no longer than 15 minutes, and occur in the area between the former office of Ian Vance and the newly reconstructed hallway to the northern wing of Site-74. 

Any personnel in the direct path between the two locations during an SCP-7000 Bludgeoning event will suffer intense blunt force trauma resulting in their death. Injury patterns have been shown to be unique to the space the victim is occupying between the two locations, indicating that two victims standing in the same location during two separate events will result in nearly identical injuries sustained, with variations to be expected in regards to muscle mass and body type. This was later confirmed via D-Class testing. 

Due to the layout of the northern wing entrance, Bludgeoning events are able to be witnessed by outside observers, but a consistent safe zone has yet to be discovered. Camera and audio equipment within range during a Bludgeoning event will likely fail, producing static, warping images, or shutting off completely. As has been noted with previous paranormal anomalies, inconsistent battery life has been noted during any SCP-7000 activity.

**Addendum-1:** Discovery 
On January 16th, 2021 reports of moving objects and “ghostly apparitions” were received by Site Director Ray. These ghost events were spotted between the office of Ian Vance and the northern wing of Site-74 which was destroyed in the previous containment breach. MTF-59 “Greater Ghost” was sent to investigate during non-operational hours.
 
**Addendum-2:** Initial Investigation Event Summary
 
> **Event Overview:** 
> //Four members of MTF-59 (hereby referred to as Ghost-1, Ghost-2, Ghost-3, Ghost-4[[footnote]] A trained Spiritual Medium [[/footnote]]) arrive at Site-74 at 2:45am on January 23, 2021. This event summary has been compiled using the surviving body cam footage along with the testimony of the remaining members of MTF-59.//
>
>

> **<BEGIN LOG>**
> 
> **3:00:12** Door is unlocked by Site Director Ray. MTF-59 enters and begins preparing their ghost hunting equipment. 
> 
> **3:00:45** Site Director Ray locks the doors of Site-74 before entering a nearby security van to watch Site-74 cameras and to keep contact over a handheld radio transceiver. 
> 
> **3:10:12** Investigation officially begins outside of Ian Vance’s former office. Ghost-4 senses minor spirit activity. Spirit Box and EMF reader remain silent. 
> 
> **3:12:24** Office door is approached and opened. MTF-59 enters. Ghost-4 states that she feels “a much stronger ghost presence”. 
> 
> **3:12:42**  EMF reader flashes once before becoming inactive. Ghost-2 says an expletive and goes to replace the batteries.
> 
> **3:13:04** The office door is slammed open and loud footsteps can be heard. This sudden noise causes Ghost-2 to drop both the EMF reader and the batteries which roll under the desk. Ghost-1,3,4 rush out of the office. Security camera footage begins to distort, but the image is still mostly visible.  
> 
> **3:13:24** Site Director Ray attempts contact to no avail. Ghost-1 and -3 begin to follow a “ghostly apparition” as Ghost-4 activates Anomalous Item-13 to work as a minor protective charm. She begins to ask questions as she walks forward.
> 
> **3:15:16** The camera facing the entrance of the northern wing of Site-74 reactivates showing Ghost-1 and -3 stopped and catching their breath. Ghost-3 has pulled out a thermal camera and has begun to search the reconstructed hallway. 
> 
> **3:16:02** Ghost-4 has caught up to them and is located approximately 30ft from the hallway. The camera then begins to distort, causing the image over the hallway to become obfuscated.
> 
> **3:16:15** Ghost-4 hears a loud series of cracks, before turning to see Ghost-3 fall to the floor in a pile of blood[[footnote]] Later examination would prove the cause of death to be blunt force trauma, similar to those caught under rubble doing natural disasters. [[/footnote]]. Ghost-1 turns to run back towards Ghost-4, but his leg begins to crush underneath him, causing him to fall onto his walkie-talkie. Dr. Israel Ray is able to hear screaming along with several heavy cracks before the walkie-talkie is presumably crushed. Ghost-1 is not visible on the camera, but blood splatter is able to be made out before the image turns off. 
> 
> **3:16:20** Ghost-4 has now begun chanting and slowly backing away. Ghost-2 arrives and begins chanting with her.[[footnote]] This chant has been identified as a minor banishment charm to subdue entities for a short amount of time. [[/footnote]]
> 
> **3:16:34** Ghost-4 begins to scream as her arm begins to crush. Causing her to drop Anomalous Item-13. 
> 
> **3:16:58** The chant finishes and a loud slam is heard. Ghost-4 falls to the ground in shock, rapidly losing blood from her crushed appendage.
> 
> **3:20:05** Dr. Israel Ray unlocks the door for Ghost-2 and -4 as they are both taken to receive medical treatment.
> 
> **<END LOG>**
> 
> **Event Outcome:** Following Event 7000-1, the reopening of the Northern Wing was postponed indefinitely. Administrative work happening near or around the former office of Ian Vance was to be relocated and all Euclid Class anomalous objects were to be relocated off-site, if possible.

