**Addendum-6: Review of the following 42 Game Session events.**
After the first game night event, no spectral sightings were reported or caught on film. This would continue until Session #8, when Tony McKay missed this session for “unspecified reasons”.[[footnote]] It was later discovered that he was absent in order to see a movie premiere with his girlfriend that same night. [[/footnote]] SCP-7000 did not make contact during the game. Israel Ray tried to continue the game but ended early, due to it “not feeling the same”. It should be noted the following week, SCP-7000 activity was reported between the office and the northern wing hallway, resulting in the death of one Junior Researcher. Session #9 proceeded as normal and SCP-7000 “out-of-game” activity again ceased. Experimenting with subbing in new players was proven to be successful in Session #12, when Andre Merritt was out sick.

As these Game Sessions continued, SCP-7000 began to gain more competence in these sessions, being able to roll dice on its own, and, as of Session #22, SCP-7000 became able to communicate through a spirit box. Communication has been rudimentary and simple, but a noticeable progression in the language used has been noted.

**Addendum-7: Downtime Incident**
Previously, Isreal Ray had been granted 4 additional hours of access to SCP-7000 for “game prep.” In the weeks following Session #22, a lack of efficient administrative work and significant clerical errors were noted[[footnote]] Including late approval on containment procedures, simple spelling and grammatical errors when updating entries, and including the stats for a D&D 5th Edition “Beholder” in the documents of SCP-████ [[/footnote]]. As reported by Site-74 personnel, Ray spent an increasing amount of time in his office and was less focused on conversations around work. 

Site-74 Head of Internal Affairs confirmed that Israel Ray was prepping for Game Session events during his work hours, thus using his additional SCP-7000 access to communicate freely with it. When confronted with this, Ray displayed anger and denied the accusation. 

Israel Ray was placed on a 2-week administrative leave as a disciplinary measure, only being allowed back on site for Game Session events. Following this, additional time with SCP-7000 was limited to one hour before or after sessions.

